{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"4a28e76a-3429-54b4-a121-7e127e8d1ed9","html":"<p>Media queries are a huge part of our daily life as web developers, and yet, most of us have only touched the surface when it comes to what they can do.  </p>\n<p>For those who aren‚Äôt familiar with the concept, let me explain it briefly.</p>\n<h2 id=\"what-are-media-queries\"><a href=\"#what-are-media-queries\" aria-label=\"what are media queries permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>What are media queries?</h2>\n<p>To illustrate, try changing the size of your browser‚Äôs window. As you move it around, you‚Äôll notice that the size and positions of elements often move based on the width and height of your screen.<br>\nThis is done thanks to <strong>media queries</strong> who‚Äôs job is to modify your site‚Äôs layout based on a device‚Äôs general type or on certain parameters (such as its size).</p>\n<p>The general syntax of media queries goes as follows:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token atrule\"><span class=\"token rule\">@media</span> screen and <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token property\">min-width</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 685px<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token selector\">.title</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">font-size</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 2rem<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">screen</code> is the media type to which the styles will apply. This media query is intended for screens.</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">and</code> is a logical operator, you can chain them as much as you want. For example, you could have a media query for <code class=\"language-text\">min-width: 685px</code> <strong>and</strong> <code class=\"language-text\">orientation: landscape</code>.</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">min-width:</code> is a media feature, in this example it tells our browser to apply the styles between the two brackets only when reaching a minimum width of 685 pixels. You can use many unit types, such as <code class=\"language-text\">rem</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Alright, let‚Äôs go over what <code class=\"language-text\">@media</code> queries can really do through concrete examples on Codepen üëá</p>\n<h2 id=\"media-types\"><a href=\"#media-types\" aria-label=\"media types permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Media types</h2>\n<p>Most of us know of the <code class=\"language-text\">screen</code> media type, but there are two other lesser known types.</p>\n<p>Media types simply describe the category of a device. By default, the <code class=\"language-text\">all</code> type is used except when using the <code class=\"language-text\">not</code> or <code class=\"language-text\">only</code> logical operators.</p>\n<h3 id=\"all\"><a href=\"#all\" aria-label=\"all permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><code class=\"language-text\">all</code></h3>\n<p>Means the styles in the query are suitable for all devices.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://codepen.io/christopherkade/pen/XLzgXX\">Codepen</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"print\"><a href=\"#print\" aria-label=\"print permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><code class=\"language-text\">print</code></h3>\n<p>Means the styles in the query are intended for paged material and documents viewed on a screen in print preview mode.<br>\nFor example, if we have a ‚Äúreservation confirmation‚Äù page we‚Äôd like for our user to print, we could hide the social media links at the bottom using this media query.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://codepen.io/christopherkade/pen/XLzgEp\">Codepen</a></p>\n<p>Right clicking and trying to print this page should display the preview without the bottom text.</p>\n<h3 id=\"screen\"><a href=\"#screen\" aria-label=\"screen permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><code class=\"language-text\">screen</code></h3>\n<p>Our usual go-to. Means the styles are intended for screens.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://codepen.io/christopherkade/pen/RzjZxb\">Codepen</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"speech\"><a href=\"#speech\" aria-label=\"speech permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><code class=\"language-text\">speech</code></h3>\n<p>This type is intended for screen readers.<br>\nA very limited amount of CSS attributes have an impact on screen reader behavior but it‚Äôs worth knowing this type. You could, for example, hide a specific element of the screen that shouldn‚Äôt be read by screen readers or have code punctuation be read out loud.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://codepen.io/christopherkade/pen/ZdaJmo\">Codepen</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"essential-media-features\"><a href=\"#essential-media-features\" aria-label=\"essential media features permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Essential media features</h2>\n<p>I won‚Äôt cover the full list of media features, as some of them are obscure and have very little use-cases. If you‚Äôre interested in the full list, check it out <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Media_Queries/Using_media_queries#Media_features\">here</a>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"width-and-height\"><a href=\"#width-and-height\" aria-label=\"width and height permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><code class=\"language-text\">width</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">height</code></h3>\n<p>Our bread and butter, these features allow us to apply styles based on the width and height of our viewport.<br>\nFor example, <a href=\"http://dev.to\">DEV</a> hides the <code class=\"language-text\">navigation</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">newest listings</code> side views when reaching respectively <code class=\"language-text\">950px</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">1120px</code> (try it out yourself !).</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://codepen.io/christopherkade/pen/ZdrgzY\">Codepen</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"orientation\"><a href=\"#orientation\" aria-label=\"orientation permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><code class=\"language-text\">orientation</code></h3>\n<p>As the name suggests, it allows us to apply styles based on the orientation of a device. Either <code class=\"language-text\">portrait</code> or <code class=\"language-text\">landscape</code>.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://codepen.io/christopherkade/pen/ZdxgVO\">Codepen</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"display-mode\"><a href=\"#display-mode\" aria-label=\"display mode permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><code class=\"language-text\">display-mode</code></h3>\n<p>Applies styles based on the display mode of an application.<br>\nAvailable modes are: <code class=\"language-text\">fullscreen</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">standalone</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">minimal-ui</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">browser</code>. <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@media/display-mode#Syntax\">More information</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token atrule\"><span class=\"token rule\">@media</span> all and <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token property\">display-mode</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> fullscreen<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token selector\">body</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">margin</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 0<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">border</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 5px solid black<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"complex-media-queries\"><a href=\"#complex-media-queries\" aria-label=\"complex media queries permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Complex media queries</h2>\n<p>With the use of logical operators such as <code class=\"language-text\">and</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">not</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">only</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">,</code> (comma) we can now build complex media queries for specific use-cases.</p>\n<p>In this example, we want our video frame to take the full width and height of the screen when in landscape mode and on a tablet (for a better viewing experience):</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://codepen.io/christopherkade/pen/wLjwMv\">Codepen</a></p>\n<p>Additionally, you can use the comma to apply any given styles to multiple queries, for example:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token atrule\"><span class=\"token rule\">@media</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token property\">min-height</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 680px<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> screen and <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token property\">orientation</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> portrait<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> ... <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>I hope you‚Äôve learned at least a couple of things in this article!</p>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/media-queries","tagSlugs":["/tag/css/","/tag/tutorial/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2019-07-02","description":"Practical examples of media queries","tags":["CSS","Tutorial"],"title":"Deep dive into @media queries"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/posts/media-queries"}}